docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html — Python socket module documentation"
    - "POSIX.1-2017 — socket API specification"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Modules/socketmodule.c"
    - "CPython source: Lib/socket.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec covers: wave 255 theme — co_varnames attributes for socket Python-level functions and socket.socket.__dict__ membership checks. NEW in extra207: socket.create_connection.__code__.co_varnames.__class__.__name__=='tuple'; socket.create_connection.__code__.co_varnames.__contains__('host')==True; socket.getfqdn.__code__.co_varnames.__contains__('name')==True; socket.socket.__dict__.__contains__('accept')==True; socket.socket.__dict__.__contains__('close')==True; socket.socket.__dict__.__contains__('makefile')==True. All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "socket.create_connection.__code__.co_varnames == ('address', 'timeout', 'source_address', 'all_errors', 'host', 'port', 'exceptions', 'res', 'af', 'socktype', 'proto', 'canonname', 'sa', 'sock', 'exc') (len=15: 4 params + 11 locals). socket.create_connection.__code__.co_argcount==3 (address, timeout, source_address; all_errors is a keyword-only parameter not counted by co_argcount). Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "socket.getfqdn.__code__.co_varnames == ('name', 'hostname', 'aliases', 'ipaddrs') (len=4: 1 param + 3 locals). socket.getfqdn.__code__.co_argcount==1. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "socket.socket.__dict__ is a mappingproxy. socket.socket.__dict__.__contains__('accept')==True; '__contains__('close')==True; '__contains__('makefile')==True. accept and makefile are Python-level methods defined in Lib/socket.py; close is also defined there as a wrapper. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

